	<text>
		<body>
			<div>
				<pb facs="#facs_1" n="1"/>
				<p facs="#facs_1_r">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_1">
                            <placeName ref="geo-2643743">London</placeName>, <date when="1946-12-12">12. 12. 1946</date>
                        </l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_5">My dear <persName ref="gnd-118777378">Raymond</persName>,</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_6">Thank you very much for your</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_7">two letters, the one from <placeName ref="geo-2643743">London</placeName> and the other from <placeName ref="geo-6077243">Montreal</placeName>
                        </l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_8">I was very relieved to see from the cable which Sonja</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_9">sent me that you had arrived safely and from your letter that</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_10">it was not too much of an ordeal. But your several false</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_11">starts in <placeName ref="geo-2643743">London</placeName> must have been something of a trial.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_12">
                            <persName ref="gnd-136148662">Mrs. Hamilton</persName> described your last visit very vividly to me.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_13">She was full of self reproach because she let you go to</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_14">
                            <placeName ref="geo-6251999">Canada</placeName> without a proper breakfast and without sewing</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_15">your coat button on and I had to promise that I would</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_16">write her apologies to you. There is another woman whose</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_17">protective and maternal instincts you have thoroughly</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_18">roused. â€” I would have written to you earlier, but</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_19">according to my very unheroic fashion l went down</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_20">with a small attack of flu shortly after you went.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_21">Not, however, before l had done some tidying in your</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_22">room, taken away the things destined for me, your books</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_23">to the Taylor, calling on <persName ref="gnd-129434507">Hunt</persName> etc. - and having</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_24">my class. The letter to <persName ref="gnd-107671662">Waszink</persName> has also gone.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_25">The one to Astrue [?] has been written and will go to-day. -</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_26">Scotts have my address. - I have only come over to</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_27">
                            <placeName ref="geo-2643743">London</placeName> for two days in order to attend to various matters</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_28">and am going back to <placeName ref="geo-11524648">Oxford</placeName> tonight in order to</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_29">finish tidying up and Christmas presenting in College</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_30">I hope that the two engravings in your room of the two cultural centres in which</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_31">you have been active will keep the good Christean in you alive.</l>
					</lg>
				</p>
				<p facs="#facs_1_r_1">
					<lg>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_3">I am longing to hear more about</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_4">your adventures and activities.</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l_2">Love</l>
						<l facs="#facs_1_l">
                            <persName ref="gnd-1029912939">Lotte</persName>
                        </l>
					</lg>
				</p>
